The '''banana plantation''' on [[Ape Atoll]] is an underground area involved in the final battle in the [[Monkey Madness I]] quest, and is only accessible during the quest. It consists of a square cave containing an enormous amount of [[banana]] trees with a large [[gorilla Statue (Monkey Madness I)|gorilla statue]] at its centre. Above the trees, encircling the top of the statue, is a large, square wooden platform on which the [[Jungle demon|quest fight]] takes place.

After the fight is won, should players choose to stay in the area, it is possible to descend from the platform, down to where the banana trees are, via trapdoors at the four corners of the arena. A few small, [[poison]]ous [[spider]]s are found amongst the trees. It should be noted that the spiders' poison start at 3 [[hitpoints]], and lasts a total of 13 poison hits. When poisoned, however, it is easy to quickly pick a couple of bananas to heal.

[[File:Plantation crack.png|thumb|left|The crack at the base of the statue.]]
In the centre of the lower area is the base of the [[gorilla Statue (Monkey Madness I)|gorilla statue]]. Players can enter the base of the statue through a crack in it. Inside is [[Bonzara]], an ancient monkey who hints at a possible sequel. He offers to teleport the player out of the arena at the end of the conversation. However, the teleport puts players in the jungle on Ape Atoll, where it may be possible to be poisoned.

Although this is much closer to [[Zooknock]] than [[Ardougne Zoo]], the [[Greegree]]s do not work here.

==Trivia==
*This is the largest banana plantation in [[Gielinor]] located underground. Here, the banana trees do not have access to sunlight, and have to use the glowing fungi for {{wp|photosynthesis}}.
*When walking to the plantation, on the edge where also the trapdoors are, there are floor spikes, which have the examine "Human sieve creation".
*When the banana plantation is entered, the [[gnome]]s disappear, leaving the only options to leave the area by talking to [[Bonzara]] or using [[Home Teleport]] when you don't have any other teleport methods with you.

